cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the capacity of a class of interference relay channels and derives outer and inner bounds for the same. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with relay channels and cooperative strategies. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with decoding techniques for interference channels. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the Gaussian class of IRCs which may have applications in multimedia communication. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may have implications for the design of communication systems in engineering and science applications.
